Second Department,

May, 1939.

(May 1, 1939.) In the Matter of the Judicial Settlement of the Account of Proceedings of George R. Roe and Another, as Executors, etc., of Gelston G. Roe, Deceased, Appellants; Pierson R. Hildreth, as Receiver in Proceedings Supplementary, etc., Respondent.

Motion to dismiss appeal denied, without costs. (Matter of Gilbert, 104 N. Y. 200, 205.) Present — Hagarty, Carswell, Adel, Taylor and Close, JJ.
